            <p>Philadelphia&#44; September&#44; 1890.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>The undersigned have been asked to act as the American Committee to<lb/> secure subscriptions for the Saadia Memorial Publication.  The purposes<lb/> of the Memorial are clearly set forth in the circular issued by the General<lb/> Committee of which we enclose a translation.<lb/></p>
            <p>Nothing remains for us to add beyond expressing the hope that you will<lb/> see fit to contribute to the success of the undertaking.<lb/></p>
            <p>We desire only to emphasize the fact that this appeal is sent to a<lb/> LIMITED number of persons&#45;&#45;to scholars&#44; more or less directly interested&#44;<lb/> and to such individuals as are ready to further scientific research.<lb/>  It should be a matter of pride for us American to join the scholars and<lb/> men of the Old World in a movement&#44; which besides rendering a just tribute<lb/> to the memory of a man who left a lasting impress on his age&#44; may be<lb/> expected to do much to promote the knowledge and the scientific study of<lb/> Jewish Literature.<lb/></p>
            <p>The SUBSCRIBERS are of two kinds&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#40;a&#41; Subscribers who will obtain a complete set for ten dollars.<lb/></p>
            <p>&#40;b&#41; Patrons&#44; who for forty dollars will receive a copy of the<lb/> publication printed on PAPIER DE HOLLANDE.<lb/></p>
            <p>We enclose a subscription blank with envelope addressed to Prof.<lb/> Morris Jastrow&#44; Jr.&#44; University of Pennsylvania&#44; Philadelphia&#44; Pa.<lb/></p>
            <p>In remitting which&#44; to save complications&#44; we ask you to do at your<lb/> earliest convenience&#44; please draw your check to the order of JACOB H. SCHIFF&#44;<lb/> Treasurer&#44; but send the check &#40;or money order&#41; to the address of Prof.<lb/> Jastrow&#44; as above.  Subscriptions will also be received and forwarded by any<lb/> member of the Committee.<lb/>  Respectfully yours&#44;<lb/> MAYER SULZBERGER&#44; Chairman&#44;<lb/> B. FELSENTHAL&#44;<lb/> JACOB H. SCHIFF&#44;<lb/> RICHARD J. H. GOTTHEIL&#44;<lb/> CYRUS ADLER&#44;<lb/> MORRIS JASTROW&#44; JR.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
